result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher Ronald Phillips was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher Ronald Phillips is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher Ronald Phillips was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Christopher Ronald Phillips was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Christopher Ronald Phillips was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
